text="Inverses and invertibility in deductive systems">Inverses and invertibility in deductive systems</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Inverses to morphisms in a <fr:link
href="jms-0048.xml"
title="Deductive system"
addr="jms-0048"
type="local">deductive system</fr:link> need not be unique due to the general failure of associativity; therefore, we must be careful when speaking of “invertible maps” or “isomorphisms”. It happens that both linear and thunkable inverses <fr:link
href="jms-004N.xml"
title="Linear and thunkable inverses"
addr="jms-004N"
type="local">are unique</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:tree
